==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trass
<hw>Trass</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>tras</ets> or
Gr. <ets>trass</ets>, probably fr. It. <ets>terrazzo</ets> terrace. See
<er>Terrace</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A white to gray
volcanic tufa, formed of decomposed trachytic cinders; -- sometimes used
as a cement. Hence, a coarse sort of plaster or mortar, durable in
water, and used to line cisterns and other reservoirs of water.</def>
<altsp>[Formerly written also <asp>tarras</asp>, <asp>tarrace</asp>,
<asp>terras</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The Dutch <xex>trass</xex> is made by burning and
grinding a soft grayish rock found on the lower Rhine.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Traulism</ent>⟦br⟧
